## 10. Compliance Rules — YAML Format

```yaml
# rules/india-maharashtra.yaml
state: Maharashtra
country: India
currency: INR
working_days_per_month: 26
overtime_multiplier: 2.0

provident_fund:
  employee_rate: 0.12
  employer_rate: 0.12
  wage_ceiling: 15000        # PF calculated on min(basic, 15000)
  applicable_if_basic_lte: null  # null = always apply

esic:
  employee_rate: 0.0075
  employer_rate: 0.0325
  applicable_if_gross_lte: 21000

professional_tax:
  slabs:
    - max_salary: 10000
      monthly_tax: 0
    - max_salary: 15000
      monthly_tax: 150
    - max_salary: 999999
      monthly_tax: 200

festival_bonus:
  rate: 0.0833              # 8.33% = 1 month / 12 months
  name: "Festival Bonus"
```

---

## 11. Key Design Decisions & Constraints

| Decision | Reasoning |
|---|---|
| Python for engine | Owner is a Python/FastAPI engineer. Easier to maintain and test. |
| WhatsApp first | Every Indian micro-business uses WhatsApp. Zero new app install. |
| Face encoding not photo | Privacy. Can't reverse-engineer a face from a 128-float vector. |
| YAML for compliance rules | Non-developers (CAs, HR consultants) can contribute new state rules without touching Python. |
| JSONB snapshot on payroll line | Audit trail. Even if rules change, old payslips show what was calculated and why. |
| Docker Compose self-host | Primary distribution method. Works on ₹500/month VPS. |
| 26 working days default | Standard Indian payroll convention. Configurable per company. |
| Multi-tenant from day 1 | One deployment, multiple shop owners. Easier to offer managed SaaS later. |

---

## 12. What This Is NOT

- Not an HR system (no leave approval workflows, no performance reviews)
- Not an accounting system (no GST filing, no P&L)
- Not for companies > 20 employees (keep it focused)
- Not a replacement for a CA (compliance rules are guidelines, not legal advice)

---

## 13. Open Source Strategy

- **License:** MIT (maximum adoption)
- **Target contributors:** Python developers, CA firms, HR software consultants, developers in Tier 2 Indian cities
- **Contribution hooks:** Adding a new state's compliance YAML requires zero Python knowledge
- **Future monetisation:** Cloud-hosted version at ₹299–499/month flat fee, auto-compliance updates, WhatsApp number included

---

## 14. Environment Variables Needed

```env
# Database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://user:pass@localhost:5432/micropayroll

# Redis
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379/0

# WhatsApp Business API
WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN=
WHATSAPP_PHONE_NUMBER_ID=
WHATSAPP_WEBHOOK_VERIFY_TOKEN=   # your chosen secret for webhook verification
WHATSAPP_BUSINESS_ACCOUNT_ID=

# App
SECRET_KEY=                      # JWT signing key
FACE_MATCH_THRESHOLD=0.6         # lower = stricter face matching
SHIFT_START_WINDOW_HOURS=2       # allow check-in 2hrs around shift start
STANDARD_SHIFT_HOURS=8

# Email (optional)
SENDGRID_API_KEY=

# Storage (for temporary image processing only — images deleted after encoding)
TEMP_IMAGE_DIR=/tmp/micropayroll
```

